-- Bank Asya shares resume trade down 11.29 percent
-- By Daren Butler
-- Mon Sep 15, 2014 02:36AM EDT
-- None



ISTANBUL, Sept 15 (Reuters) - Shares in Turkish Islamic lender Bank Asya <ASYAB.IS> fell 11.29 percent to 1.1 lira on Monday as trading resumed after a suspension of more than a month.

The shares were suspended on Aug. 7 and the Istanbul stock exchange said a week later they would remain suspended until uncertainty regarding the bank's ownership was resolved. [ID:nL6N0QK1FF]